com.facetec.sdk

Class FaceTecSDK

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.facetec.sdk.FaceTecSDK

  • public final class FaceTecSDK
extends java.lang.Object
    FaceTecSDK is the main class you will use in controlling FaceTec SDK.
    This class consists of static methods that will aid in setting up FaceTec SDK for
    verification as well as give some insight as to the capabilities
    of the device which will help in setting up verification strategies.

                                               @NonNull
                                               java.lang.String deviceKeyIdentifier,

                                               @Nullable
                                               FaceTecSDK.InitializeCallback callback)
        Initializes the FaceTec SDK using your Device SDK Key Identifier. Initialize _must_ be called at least once by the application before invoking any SDK operations. This function may be called repeatedly without harm.
        Parameters:
        context - Activity context
        deviceKeyIdentifier - Identifies the client for determination of key capabilities
        faceScanEncryptionKey - Set the encryption key to be used for FaceTec Server FaceScan
        callback - Optional callback to notify caller when initialization has completed

      • getCameraPermissionStatus

        public static FaceTecSDK.CameraPermissionStatus getCameraPermissionStatus(android.content.Context context)
        Convenience method to check for android camera permissions. This function is used to check the camera permission status prior to using FaceTec SDK. If camera permission has not been previously granted, FaceTec will display a UI requesting the user to allow permission, however some applications may wish to manage camera permission themselves. Those applications should verify camera permissions prior to transitioning.
        Parameters:
        context - Activity context
        Returns:
        FaceTecSDK.CameraPermissionStatus

      • setAuditTrailType

        public static void setAuditTrailType(FaceTecAuditTrailType auditTrailType)
        Sets the type of audit trail images to be collected. If this property is not set to Disabled, a sample of some of the camera frames collected during the enrollment/authentication process on the Authentication/Enrollment response will be included. Default type is .DISABLED
        Parameters:
        auditTrailType - the type of audit trail image to be returned
